  "title": "Document Controller",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p>Ø  Receive, verify and acknowledge receipt of the documents in accordance with agreed document control procedure</p><p>Ø  Register the drawings received from Client and others.</p><p>Ø  Issue documents to Classification Societies and Owners for approval</p><p>Ø  Issue documents with transmittal to Operations and other departments</p><p>Ø  File the drawings and documents</p><p>Ø  Submission of Design Acceptance Request via LTA EPIC System (Online DAR Portal) in accordance with project document formats and requirements.</p><p>Ø  Manage and control all interface documentation and prepare updates and responds to\nclient’s request for information about project status</p><p>Ø  Create, issue and progress documents transmittal to clients, sub-con and consultants.</p><p>Ø  Maintain proper filing systems according to ISO Standard and implement project document\nmanagement system and process in accordance with company policies.</p><p>Ø  Ensure proper document classifications, sorting, filing and archiving and managed in\nstrict confidentiality.</p><p>Ø  Performs files back-up to ensure proper storage and archiving of projects records.</p><p>Ø  Assist Clients and walk in visitors</p><p>Ø  Handle incoming and outgoing calls for ALL department</p><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>1.    At least 5years LTA Project Working Experience</p><p>2.    Familiar with project management</p><p>3.    Hands-on experience with MS Office and MS Excel & Power Point</p><p>4.    Knowledge of Document Management</p><p>5.    Proficient typing and editing skills, Data organization skills</p><p>6.    Basic understanding of construction documents</p>",
